results.name: Decimal expansion of 192*K^2*G/Pi^4 = Product_{p prime congruent to 1 modulo 4} (1 + 1/p^2), where K is the Landau-Ramanujan constant and G Catalan's constant.
reference: Steven R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Cambridge University Press, 2003, Section 2.3 Landau-Ramanujan constant, p. 101.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2500
formula: 192*K^2*G/Pi^4, where K is the Landau-Ramanujan constant (A064533) and G Catalan's constant (A006752).
mathematica: digits = 101; LandauRamanujanK = 1/Sqrt[2]*NProduct[((1 - 2^(-2^n))*Zeta[2^n]/DirichletBeta[2^n])^(1/2^(n + 1)), {n, 1, 24}, WorkingPrecision -> digits + 5]; 192*LandauRamanujanK^2*Catalan/Pi^4 // RealDigits[#, 10, digits] & // First (* updated Mar 14 2018 *)
